=head1 DESCRIPTION

Represents an Amazon Redshift Serverless reservation, which gives you
the option to commit to a specified number of Redshift Processing Units
(RPUs) for a year at a discount from Serverless on-demand (OD) rates.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Capacity => Int

The number of Redshift Processing Units (RPUs) to reserve.


=head2 EndDate => Str

The end date for the serverless reservation. This date is one year
after the start date that you specify.


=head2 Offering => L<Paws::RedshiftServerless::ReservationOffering>

The type of offering for the reservation. The offering class determines
the payment schedule for the reservation.


=head2 ReservationArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) that uniquely identifies the serverless
reservation.


=head2 ReservationId => Str

The identifier that uniquely identifies the serverless reservation.


=head2 StartDate => Str

The start date for the serverless reservation. This is the date you
specified for the reservation to start when you created the
reservation.


=head2 Status => Str

The status of the reservation. Possible values include the following:

=over

=item *

C<payment-pending>

=item *

C<active>

=item *

C<payment-failed>

=item *

C<retired>

=back




